Interpolation
Property or expression within double curly braces is known as Interpolation.
e.g :- {{ name }}
       public name= "sahilDynamic";
Evalutate content inside curly braces and display value when component is rendered in browser.
Simplest way to bind data from class to template.

Interpolation Can do 
Angular evalutates the expression and displays the result. {{ 2 + 3 }}  ==> 5
String concatenation. <h2> {{"welcome "+ name }} </h2> ==> welcome sahilDynamic
Js properties. {{ name.length }} ==> 12
Js methods. <h2> {{ name.toUpperCase() }} </h2> ==> SAHILDYNAMIC
Can call methods define in component class. <h2> {{ greetUser() }} </h2>  ==> hello sahilDynamic
    
    greetUser() {
        return "hello " + this.name;
    }

Access to global variables such as windows , scrren .Do it in the class and bind it to the template.
    <h2> {{ siteUrl }} </h2> ==> http://localhost:4200/
    public siteUrl = window.location.href;

    

Interpolation Cannot do
Assigning the expression to variable. <h2> {{ a = 2 + 4 }} </h2> ==> error blank screen.(template pare error , cannot contain assignents)
Access to global variables such as windows , scrren...    <h2> {{window.location.href}} </h2> ==>  TypeError: Cannot read property 'location' of undefined.
